---
---
<section class="page-container section-spacer" data-orb="5">
  <div class="geo-divider">
    <span class="geo-circle" style="background: var(--color-geo-coral);"></span>
    <span class="geo-circle" style="background: var(--color-geo-blue);"></span>
    <span class="geo-circle" style="background: var(--color-geo-teal);"></span>
  </div>
  <p class="eyebrow fade-in">pricing</p>
  <h2 class="fade-in-up delay-1" style="max-width: 500px; margin-bottom: clamp(4rem, 8vw, 6rem);">One plan. No tiers to compare.</h2>
  <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 420px); justify-content: center; gap: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);">
    <div class="fade-in-up delay-2">
      <div style="background: var(--color-surface); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 12px; padding: 2.5rem; position: relative; overflow: hidden;">
        <div style="position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; right: 0; height: 4px; background: var(--color-geo-blue);"></div>
        <p class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">beta supporter</p>
        <p style="font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: -0.03em; margin-bottom: 0.25rem; color: var(--color-geo-blue);">$5<span style="font-size: 1.125rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);">/mo</span></p>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">One recurring plan, no tiers. Full access to elly and every update as it ships, for the whole beta.</p>
        <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
          <li style="padding: 0.375rem 0; font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-ink-secondary); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);">Full app: PWA + native installers (macOS, Windows, Linux)</li>
          <li style="padding: 0.375rem 0; font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-ink-secondary); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);">Every new feature and beta version as it ships</li>
          <li style="padding: 0.375rem 0; font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-ink-secondary); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);">Guided one-version-at-a-time updates, database always backed up first</li>
          <li style="padding: 0.375rem 0; font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-ink-secondary); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);">Direct input on what gets built next</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="https://www.patreon.com/cw/ellyai?utm_medium=unknown&utm_source=join_link&utm_campaign=creatorshare_creator&utm_content=copyLink" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn-primary" style="width: 100%; justify-content: center; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Get elly -- $5/mo</a>
        <p class="body-small" style="text-align: center;">Locked in for as long as you stay subscribed. Starting price moves to $10/mo once elly leaves beta at 1.0 -- join now to keep this rate.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <p class="body-small fade-in-up delay-3" style="margin-top: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 3.5rem); max-width: 640px;">The backend (domain logic, MCP server, REST API) is planned to become open source in its own repository once it's ready -- self-hosting the free/open core will be a real option at that point. Today, during the beta, the full polished app (dashboard, installers, and ongoing updates) is only available through the plan above.</p>
</section>
